**1. What is PL/SQL?**
PL/SQL (Procedural Language/SQL) is Oracle's procedural extension of SQL.
Combines SQL with programming features.
Used to write complete database programs.
Adds features like:
Variables
Loops
IF/CASE conditions
Exception handling
Cursors
Procedures
Functions
Packages
Triggers

Definition:

PL/SQL is a block-structured programming language developed by Oracle that extends SQL with procedural programming capabilities.

2. Why PL/SQL?

SQL can:

Retrieve and manipulate data.

SQL cannot:

Repeat statements (loops)
Make decisions (IF)
Store values (variables)
Handle errors
Create reusable programs

PL/SQL overcomes these limitations.

3. Importance of PL/SQL
A. Reduces Network Traffic
Multiple SQL statements are sent as one PL/SQL block.
Fewer database calls.
B. Better Performance
Entire block executes together.
Faster execution.
Less communication overhead.
C. Code Reusability
Write procedures/functions once.
Reuse whenever needed.
D. Exception Handling
Handles runtime errors using EXCEPTION block.
Prevents program termination.
E. Security
Users execute procedures instead of directly accessing tables.
Better access control.
F. Business Logic
Enforces business rules.
Example: Prevent negative salary.
