6. SQL vs PL/SQL
SQL	PL/SQL
Query language	Procedural language
Executes one statement	Executes block of statements
No variables	Supports variables
No loops	Supports loops
No IF/CASE	Supports IF/CASE
No exception handling	Supports exceptions
Cannot create procedures/functions	Can create procedures/functions
Less reusable	Highly reusable
